main

Class Controller

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.application.Application
      • main.Controller

  • public class Controller
extends javafx.application.Application
    The main controller class of the JavaFX program. Contains both the main(String[]) function to be run by JVM, and the Application.start() function to be run by JavaFX. Also handles the creation and management of JavaFX Application Thread and the Task thread.

      • startUploaderTask

        public void startUploaderTask(java.lang.String hostname,
                              int port,
                              java.lang.String username,
                              java.lang.String password,
                              java.lang.String uploadPath,
                              boolean reuseSsl,
                              boolean passiveMode,
                              boolean implicit,
                              boolean printErrors,
                              java.util.List<java.io.File> files)
        Starts the Task Thread that executes the FTP file upload.
        Parameters:
        hostname - Hostname for the FTP server.
        port - Port for the FTP server.
        username - Username for the FTP server login.
        password - Password for the FTP server login.
        uploadPath - Path on FTP server to upload to.
        reuseSsl - Reuse or create new SSL context for upload connection.
        passiveMode - Passive or active mode for the FTP server.
        implicit - Implicit or explicit connection for the FTP server.
        printErrors - Redirect error PrintStream for errors, used for debugging error messages.
        files - File(s) to upload to the FTP server.

      • cancelUploaderTask

        public void cancelUploaderTask()
        Attempts to cancel the FTP file upload. First attempts to send FTP command "ABOR" to server. Prints error stack trace if IOException is thrown/caught. Then sets the Task state to "CANCELLED"
